---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Zcompress | 100% Private PDF Compressor"
  description="Read the Privacy Policy of Zcompress. Learn how Zcompress processes your PDF files entirely client-side inside your browser with 100% privacy and security."
  ogUrl="https://zcompress.com/privacy"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-canvas-soft text-ink py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-b border-hairline pb-8">
        <span class="text-caption-mono font-mono text-link-deep uppercase tracking-wider block mb-3">
          Security & Privacy
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-display-lg md:text-display-xl text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-1.5px] md:tracking-[-2.4px] mb-4">
          Privacy Policy.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-body-lg text-body">
          Last updated: June 26, 2026. Learn why Zcompress is 100% secure, zero-server-upload, and completely private by design.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <article class="space-y-10">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] mb-4">
            1. 100% Local Processing.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            Zcompress is built on a "zero-trust" architecture. Unlike traditional online PDF compressors, Zcompress does <strong>not</strong> upload your documents to any remote servers. All file optimization, rendering, downsampling, and conversion happen entirely within your local web browser's memory sandbox.
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            Your files never leave your computer. This means your sensitive business data, personal identification documents, and private contracts are completely safe from interception, data breaches, or server-side logging.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] mb-4">
            2. Personal Data We Do Not Collect.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            Because our service operates client-side, we do not require, collect, or store:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-body-md text-body mb-6">
            <li>Your PDF files or any content contained within them.</li>
            <li>Your name, email address, phone number, or billing information.</li>
            <li>User accounts or authentication credentials (no registration is required).</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            You are completely anonymous when using Zcompress.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] mb-4">
            3. Local Storage & Theme Preferences.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            We use your browser's local storage (LocalStorage) solely to remember your UI theme preference (dark mode vs. light mode). This data is stored locally on your device and is never transmitted to us or any third party.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] mb-4">
            4. Third-Party Libraries & CDNs.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            Zcompress relies on verified, open-source JavaScript libraries to function:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-body-md text-body mb-6">
            <li><strong>pdf-lib</strong>: Used for editing, copying, and compressing PDF files.</li>
            <li><strong>pdf.js</strong>: Created by Mozilla, used for rendering PDF pages to image canvas elements.</li>
            <li><strong>jszip</strong>: Used to bundle multiple compressed files into a single ZIP archive for bulk download.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            These libraries are loaded dynamically from public Content Delivery Networks (CDNs) such as Cloudflare (cdnjs) and unpkg. Your browser may log connection metadata with these networks when fetching the library files, which is subject to their respective privacy policies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] mb-4">
            5. Changes to This Policy.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed">
            We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. Since we do not collect user contact information, we recommend checking this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your privacy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-8">
          <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] mb-4">
            Questions?
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
            If you have any questions or concerns regarding our privacy practices, please contact us.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas text-body-sm-strong text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2/50 transition-colors shadow-level-2 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
          >
            Go to Contact Us
          </a>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
